   3.810110941872168*^9, 3.8101110800488815`*^9}, 3.8101133155103245`*^9, {
   3.810113494547086*^9, 3.810113538835008*^9}, 3.8101135907593746`*^9, {
   3.8101142031650095`*^9, 3.8101142093375626`*^9}, {3.8101143688165503`*^9, 
   3.810114387604743*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6a611dfb-6c4c-4774-a213-\
93a757042f68"],

Cell["and the kinetic energy is given by", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810114399428561*^9, 3.810114405600547*^9}, {
  3.915801336704365*^9, 
  3.915801337723648*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2c4df16d-8141-43ad-b02c-\
064e611935b8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["T",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
  FractionBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["L",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
   RowBox[{"2", 
    StyleBox["I",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810108783183482*^9, 3.810108815266238*^9}, {
  3.8101088632448235`*^9, 3.8101088893706894`*^9}, {3.8101114824558687`*^9, 
  3.810111559886958*^9}, {3.8101132073667517`*^9, 3.810113282146639*^9}, {
  3.810113340959403*^9, 3.8101133457491274`*^9}, {3.8101144218981457`*^9, 
  3.81011442986573*^9}, {3.915801311906958*^9, 
  3.9158013127831154`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ae231662-ffeb-41c6-8daf-\
6a00cbfa71a7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving the Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger Equation for a Rigid Rotor", \
"Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101124726022263`*^9, 3.810112476509534*^9}, {
  3.810114444598981*^9, 
  3.8101144530247173`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e0294ef9-c2f1-4d7a-b6a1-\
7bed75ba7a3e"],

Cell["\<\
We now need to write down the form of the time-independent \
Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation for the rigid rotor. The Hamiltonian \
operator can be written as the sum of the kinetic and potential energy \
operators,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810114516487426*^9, 
  3.810114593998664*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9ad85f40-a5e0-47fd-9deb-\
c119cb7cc9e6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  OverscriptBox[
   StyleBox["H",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "+", 
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 
  3.810114640337751*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e7c9c0dc-3c3a-44ca-a6c1-\
17329206e11a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We are discussing a rigid-rotor that is not in a potential, so ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "=", "0"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"21972263-d36a-4002-810d-ac7e7d962897"],
 ", and we can write"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146490738077`*^9, 
  3.810114682493128*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"34c177e1-3d4c-44c9-a7e9-\
7b14ae3f5449"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  OverscriptBox[
   StyleBox["H",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
      SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}], 
     RowBox[{"2", "\[Mu]"}]], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 
  3.8101147298453236`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"23ab829d-0f75-4244-a56f-\
69f559203671"],

Cell["Recall that in Cartesian coordinates, ", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810114768698268*^9, 3.810114775304448*^9}, {
  3.841418256119215*^9, 
  3.8414182565190725`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"59095d61-ae7e-4bbe-9721-\
5fbf726ea481"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"], "=", 
   FractionBox[
    SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}]]}], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
   RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
    SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
   RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
    SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
  3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
  3.8101148337760096`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"67c4ba7f-d7af-478a-9d14-\
497198ef4827"],

Cell["\<\
However, because we are working in a rotational coordinate, we want to use \
spherical rather than Cartesian coordinates. The transformation of the \
Laplacian to spherical coordinates is rather involved, so only the end result \
is given here. The Laplacian in spherical coordinates is written\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101148206480083`*^9, 3.810114865543086*^9}, {
  3.8101149444101353`*^9, 3.81011495793641*^9}, {3.8101154571536036`*^9, 
  3.8101154900392675`*^9}, {3.841418278238491*^9, 3.8414182786065636`*^9}, {
  3.915801402259855*^9, 
  3.9158014035064*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7f1fb025-f0d6-477b-895e-ca72f977a7de"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"], "=", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["r",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]]}], 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], 
    SubscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox[
        StyleBox["r",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
       FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
         StyleBox["r",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]}]]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], "+", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["r",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], "sin", 
     RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]], 
    SubscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"sin", 
       RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
       FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["r",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], "+", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["r",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
     SuperscriptBox["sin", "2"], 
     RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
   SubscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     FractionBox[
      SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}]], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["r",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", "\[Theta]"}]]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
   3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
   3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, 
   3.8101157585076213`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"3030a83a-1d22-483c-9e8f-\
2aa47b100c1d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Fortunately, in the case of the rigid rotor, ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is a constant, which slightly simplifies the Laplacian to the form"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101156843031397`*^9, 3.810115720525422*^9}, {
  3.8101157650276384`*^9, 
  3.8101157658698535`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"68829112-04db-4982-9fe4-\
9f95c01dea65"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"], "=", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], "sin", 
      RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]]}], 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"sin", 
      RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
      FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
       RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], "+", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["r",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
     SuperscriptBox["sin", "2"], 
     RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    FractionBox[
     SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}]], ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
   3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
   3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
   3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, 
   3.810116943371087*^9},ExpressionUUID->"3d9b86e6-9ce1-4c4a-b94d-\
7694e84af13a"],

Cell["\<\
Now, we can use the relation between reduced mass, angular momentum, and \
length of rotor in equation (57) to write that \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101158631363726`*^9, 3.810115920986212*^9}, {
  3.91580153926659*^9, 3.915801539924372*^9}, {3.9158059365531907`*^9, 
  3.9158059671217136`*^9}, {3.9161626415534124`*^9, 3.916162642013137*^9}, {
  3.9351471300663605`*^9, 
  3.935147130239496*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"768af8ee-8e43-4e95-8353-\
ece60ca6b6b1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
    SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}], 
   RowBox[{"2", "\[Mu]"}]], "=", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
     SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["r",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}], 
   RowBox[{"2", 
    StyleBox["I",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cd71cc24-7508-41e1-9327-\
8252adcf0bf3"],

Cell["and we can write the Hamiltonian as", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101160108599634`*^9, 
  3.8101160156100655`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8f0f22ed-b850-4bd0-b465-\
27f57c935b40"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  OverscriptBox[
   StyleBox["H",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
     SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}], 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["1", 
      RowBox[{"sin", 
       RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
       RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"sin", 
        RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
        FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
         RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["1", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["sin", "2"], 
       RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      FractionBox[
       SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
       RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
        SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}]], ")"}]}]}], 
   "]"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
   3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
   3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
   3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
   3.810116055282401*^9}, 
   3.8101169396100073`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"254e2e67-4208-4efb-bf0c-\
1fa6b8e8ccdf"],

Cell["We also note here that (for this particular system)", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101163590045614`*^9, 3.810116425706046*^9}, {
  3.9164987996672654`*^9, 
  3.9164988041993947`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f0168927-3239-4a28-9add-\
f27d3940e613"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  OverscriptBox[
   StyleBox["H",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "=", 
  FractionBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["L",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "2"], 
   RowBox[{"2", 
    StyleBox["I",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
  3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
  3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
  3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
  3.810116055282401*^9}, {3.8101163980156183`*^9, 
  3.8101164366595163`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7e3df7f3-36d6-4f81-99d8-\
b53910988d3e"],

Cell["\<\
where we have used the fact that the Hamiltonian in this case only contains a \
kinetic energy term and have replaced the classical form of equation (59) \
with its quantum-mechanical operator equivalent. Using this observation, we \
can also write that\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810116442942041*^9, 3.810116500008525*^9}, {
  3.8737915369973106`*^9, 3.873791537322954*^9}, {3.915801575556834*^9, 
  3.91580157610242*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"905333f5-c41d-4ed9-b4bc-\
3834954a8e24"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox[
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["L",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "2"], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       RowBox[{"sin", 
        RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]], 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"sin", 
         RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
         FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
          RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox["sin", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox[
        SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
         SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}]], ")"}]}]}], 
    "]"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
   3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
   3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
   3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
   3.810116055282401*^9}, {3.8101165098276663`*^9, 3.810116511942164*^9}, 
   3.8101169355096436`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"dd99067a-e1b7-4e1a-b351-\
a892cf9e2208"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll come back to this later. For now, we still need to \
write down the TISE and solve. When we have a function that only depends on \
the angles \[Phi] and \[Theta], we typically write it with ",
 StyleBox["Y",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " instead of the more common \[Psi], so we will write the Hamiltonian as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810116545342147*^9, 
  3.8101166577416673`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eb4df3a2-d5c9-4afb-9689-\
d2a5a4fcde57"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["H",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
   StyleBox["Y",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["EY",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
  3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
  3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
  3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
  3.810116055282401*^9}, {3.810116669328328*^9, 
  3.8101167076580467`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3eb1b4bc-7920-41de-824c-\
86fc67a97428"],

Cell["or, in the longer form,", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101167133260374`*^9, 
  3.8101167252887917`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"61657964-c2cc-47db-839d-\
2bc5cf7cc9d3"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
      SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}], 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      StyleBox["I",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       RowBox[{"sin", 
        RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]], 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"sin", 
         RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
         FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
          RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox["sin", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox[
        SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
         SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}]], ")"}]}]}], "]"}], 
   StyleBox["Y",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["EY",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
   3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
   3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
   3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
   3.810116055282401*^9}, {3.810116669328328*^9, 3.8101167373939514`*^9}, 
   3.8101169307892475`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"eddfa7e7-8d1d-4116-af8e-\
f8795df43013"],

Cell["\<\
Now we use a couple of tricks to simplify this equation. First we define a \
new constant \[Beta] as\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810116780820096*^9, 
  3.8101167939539375`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5213344c-2adc-47f0-9bed-\
de9d39d210a8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "=", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"2", 
    StyleBox["IE",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 
  3.8101168261777344`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4dfe7984-2b2b-42df-9ee3-\
90dc410bfd57"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Next, we multiply both sides of the equation by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["sin", "2"], "(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"d195c15c-c134-4a9b-8c0a-ded41e8a4c40"],
 ". Together, these operations give us the result"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101168286658792`*^9, 
  3.810116861864035*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"66c84989-e80c-4cb5-bbf7-\
cc18fcbecd82"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"-", 
    RowBox[{"[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"sin", 
       RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
       RowBox[{
        FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
         RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]], 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"sin", 
          RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
          FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
           RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], "+", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox[
        SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
         SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}]], ")"}]}], "]"}]}], 
   StyleBox["Y",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Beta]",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   StyleBox[" ",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], 
   RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
   StyleBox["Y",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
  3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
  3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
  3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
  3.810116055282401*^9}, {3.810116669328328*^9, 3.8101167373939514`*^9}, {
  3.8101169029251204`*^9, 3.8101169131159315`*^9}, {3.810116961251155*^9, 
  3.8101169930769873`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"601c0d7d-3d02-41ed-8164-\
f96378e24e88"],

Cell["Or", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101170081777782`*^9, 
  3.8101170083077707`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f9e21701-8075-4d5b-b40c-\
2135c6e8d13e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"sin", 
    RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["\[PartialD]", 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"sin", 
       RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
       FractionBox[
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
          StyleBox["Y",
           FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}], 
        RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Theta]"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], "+", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "2"], 
      StyleBox["Y",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}]], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Beta]",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox[" ",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["sin",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
    StyleBox["Y",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}]}], "=", 
  "0"}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
  3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
  3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
  3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
  3.810116055282401*^9}, {3.810116669328328*^9, 3.8101167373939514`*^9}, {
  3.8101169029251204`*^9, 3.8101169131159315`*^9}, {3.810116961251155*^9, 
  3.8101169930769873`*^9}, {3.8101170244657636`*^9, 
  3.810117042845109*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d6432e6a-b81e-411f-a79e-\
d5536513d4a6"],

Cell["\<\
This differential equation can be solved exactly through separation of \
variables, although it is a bit time-intensive. Because this same \
differential equation will be central to the solutions of the hydrogen atom, \
we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll defer a more thorough discussion of the form of the \
solutions until then. For now, we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll discuss the restraints \
imposed on the energy of the system as a result of finding the solutions to \
equation (72).\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81011715503741*^9, 3.810117172999729*^9}, {
  3.810117486164733*^9, 3.8101175973955607`*^9}, {3.841418784896823*^9, 
  3.8414187887428064`*^9}, {3.9158060343235903`*^9, 3.915806035170111*^9}, {
  3.9161627046063156`*^9, 3.9161627047517195`*^9}, {3.935147468422163*^9, 
  3.935147478566204*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e75e5d06-2f1a-4072-9189-\
7056db3b8cfc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Energy Eigenvalues of the Rigid Rotor", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101124726022263`*^9, 3.810112476509534*^9}, {
  3.810114444598981*^9, 3.8101144530247173`*^9}, {3.810117640670355*^9, 
  3.8101176463721848`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"374a097c-426f-4a5c-984c-\
1bbddaa81775"],

Cell["\<\
When we solve equation (72), which, recall, gives us the solutions of the \
TISE,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101176785079374`*^9, 3.8101176998909583`*^9}, {
  3.9158062745688963`*^9, 3.915806275392562*^9}, {3.9161627099211073`*^9, 
  3.916162710076438*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f6037251-492c-4aeb-8151-\
6ac10e90bd86"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["H",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
   StyleBox["Y",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["EY",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079734359242287`*^9, 3.8079734595866747`*^9}, {
  3.8079735259616528`*^9, 3.807973556017437*^9}, {3.8101148246033597`*^9, 
  3.8101148337760096`*^9}, {3.8101155026418304`*^9, 3.810115681440522*^9}, {
  3.8101157378400974`*^9, 3.810115762443446*^9}, {3.81011602854877*^9, 
  3.810116055282401*^9}, {3.810116669328328*^9, 
  3.8101167076580467`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4bcf01f2-b476-47dc-99b2-\
86a24638863c"],

Cell["\<\
we find that again our solutions impose a constraint on the allowed energy \
values. This constraint takes the form\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101177147313104`*^9, 
  3.8101177617290993`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1dbfef54-24e4-480a-b540-\
04224e4c11d2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["J",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["J",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["+",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], 
       StyleBox["1",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
     StyleBox["            ",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["J",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "=", "0"}]}], ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", ",",
   " ", "..."}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
  3.81011776826762*^9, 
  3.8101177880720615`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6f268157-51dd-4863-bc55-\
b9bdbf2b303f"],

Cell["\<\
Remember that \[Beta] is proportional to the energy (see equation 71), so we \
can write down the corresponding constraints on the energy as\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810117794425771*^9, 3.810117847907257*^9}, {
  3.9158062918982706`*^9, 3.915806298432007*^9}, {3.9158069397156367`*^9, 
  3.915806952793109*^9}, {3.9161627167148247`*^9, 3.916162716889389*^9}, {
  3.9351474891564693`*^9, 
  3.9351474894898396`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2d0382a3-523d-4307-a824-\
5e0de1c5d801"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox["E", "J"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox[
      SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
      RowBox[{"2", 
       StyleBox["I",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], 
     StyleBox["J",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["J",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["+",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], 
       StyleBox["1",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
     StyleBox["            ",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["J",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "=", "0"}]}], ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", ",",
   " ", "..."}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
   3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
   3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
   3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
   3.8101179041283765`*^9}, 
   3.810118893408634*^9},ExpressionUUID->"7d27f2ec-47c1-43d0-8a9f-\
316ea8dbb878"],

Cell["\<\
As in the other quantum-mechanical systems, we have only discrete values for \
the energy. Each energy level is actually degenerate, meaning that there are \
multiple eigenfunctions with the same energy, and the degeneracy is given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810117977261583*^9, 3.8101180519186845`*^9}, {
  3.810118114392614*^9, 3.810118136850959*^9}, {3.841418940951063*^9, 
  3.841418942371519*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5e9d94f8-b6b2-4864-8ddb-\
fd08115960ea"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox["g", "J"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"2", 
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
     StyleBox["+",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["1",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["            ",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}], "=", "0"}]}], ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", 
  ",", " ", "..."}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
  3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
  3.8101179041283765`*^9}, {3.8101181436662183`*^9, 
  3.8101181537719917`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9335524c-1e8e-4e88-bd83-\
774d20a956b7"],

Cell["\<\
We will see the same degeneracy result in the hydrogen atom. Note that the \
fact that there are discrete energies also implies that there are discrete \
values for the angular momentum (or rather, the square of the angular \
momentum). \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810118169343548*^9, 3.8101181829270916`*^9}, {
  3.810118251361841*^9, 3.810118324046734*^9}, {3.8101183849695473`*^9, 
  3.8101184529098873`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"329a3598-8f9c-47db-bb44-\
f0bebad333f5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
The Rigid Rotor as a Model for Rotation of Diatomic Molecules\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101124726022263`*^9, 3.810112476509534*^9}, {
  3.810114444598981*^9, 3.8101144530247173`*^9}, {3.810117640670355*^9, 
  3.8101176463721848`*^9}, {3.8101185944469457`*^9, 
  3.8101186063310037`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d6a0b3b4-059a-4254-ab68-\
67e5ab37ad70"],

Cell["\<\
We can directly apply the rigid rotor model to interpret the rotational \
energy levels of a diatomic molecule.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810118613479906*^9, 
  3.810118737096867*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ae975e78-d46d-48de-9303-\
743a68d76c85"],

Cell["\<\
In the case of the harmonic oscillator, all of the energy levels are equally \
spaced. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101187396296635`*^9, 3.81011874227099*^9}, {
   3.8101188350541625`*^9, 3.8101188554494314`*^9}, 
   3.9158063597047596`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"82784a94-8fd5-48f6-8026-\
6a950720eed0"],

Cell["\<\
The rotational energy levels of a molecule are a different case. We can see \
that the energy spacing between any two adjacent energy levels is given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101187447981005`*^9, 
  3.8101187765740833`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d471ba25-ea41-43d8-baf8-\
6aa533614f7a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{"J", "+", "1"}]], "-", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "J"]}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      StyleBox["I",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["+",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        StyleBox["1",
         FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["+",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        StyleBox["2",
         FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}], 
     StyleBox["-",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["+",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        StyleBox["1",
         FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}]}], 
    StyleBox["]",
     FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
  3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
  3.8101179041283765`*^9}, {3.810118784045661*^9, 3.8101188159834547`*^9}, {
  3.8101188693749995`*^9, 
  3.8101189018153963`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3c00f4cb-b857-413b-91a6-\
249d3731b4f8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\t\t        ", 
  RowBox[{"=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["+",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["1",
       FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
  3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
  3.8101179041283765`*^9}, {3.810118784045661*^9, 3.8101188159834547`*^9}, {
  3.8101188693749995`*^9, 
  3.81011893238441*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"90df2739-2e1b-4048-b261-\
b38afb919a2e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Thus, as ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " increases, the spacing between adjacent levels also increases. In \
addition, the difference in energy levels is typically quite small, so you \
have many initially populated states. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101189728584146`*^9, 3.8101189846551237`*^9}, {
  3.810119018563933*^9, 
  3.810119060555586*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cee0c8ea-dd1e-4a13-bda5-\
ae6623204e3d"],

Cell["\<\
Fortunately, when we talk about spectroscopy we will see that transitions are \
only allowed between adjacent energy levels, so the spectrum of a diatomic \
only resembles an envelope of equally-spaced lines. We will discuss these \
topics more later in the course.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810119064713377*^9, 
  3.8101191364876537`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6baf4e02-7f54-423a-981e-\
a8b4ea55a928"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
